@SteamShon I found an error situation during my retest with my colleague.

`rm -rf var storage ; sbt 'project s2core' 'test'`

The result of the above test is non-deterministic. 
There are times when it succeeds and when it fails.



I'll find out the exact cause and comment again.

```
# Log if `edge element type` test fails
[info]  
Some(GlobalIndex(Some(1),edge,WrappedArray(_eid_, _label_, _serviceColumn_, _service_, _vid_, weight),S2GraphTest2)) 
  was not equal to 
Some(GlobalIndex(Some(4),edge,WrappedArray(_eid_, _label_, _serviceColumn_, _service_, _vid_, age, name, weight),test-1)) 

(GlobalIndexTest.scala:56)
```

```
# Log if `vertex element type` test fails
[info]  
Some(GlobalIndex(Some(2),vertex,WrappedArray(_eid_, _label_, _serviceColumn_, _service_, _vid_, date, name, weight),test_global)) 
  was not equal to 
Some(GlobalIndex(Some(6),vertex,WrappedArray(_eid_, _label_, _serviceColumn_, _service_, _vid_, age, name, weight),test-1)) 

(GlobalIndexTest.scala:63)
```




### Below is a record of the case where the cause is found incorrectly

~~~In a clean environment, if the test fails with the above command, the first execution fails and the next execution succeeds.~~~

~~I've found a bug in the code below.~~

```scala
  def findAll(elementType: String, useCache: Boolean = true)(implicit session: DBSession = AutoSession): Seq[GlobalIndex] = {
    lazy val ls = sql"""select * from global_indices where element_type = $elementType""".map { rs => GlobalIndex(rs) }.list.apply
    if (useCache) {
      listCache.withCache(s"findAll:elementType=$elementType") {
        putsToCache(ls.map { globalIndex =>
          val cacheKey = s"elementType=${globalIndex.elementType}:indexName=${globalIndex.indexName}"
          cacheKey -> globalIndex
        })
        ls
      }
    } else {
      ls
    }
  }
```

~~The above method does not return `ls` in the `useCache` situation (`ls` is updated in the background thread)~~

~~I have changed the code below to fix it.~~

```scala
  def findAll(elementType: String, useCache: Boolean = true)(implicit session: DBSession = AutoSession): Seq[GlobalIndex] = {
    lazy val ls = sql"""select * from global_indices where element_type = $elementType""".map { rs => GlobalIndex(rs) }.list.apply
    if (useCache) {
      listCache.withCache(s"findAll:elementType=$elementType") {
        putsToCache(ls.map { globalIndex =>
          val cacheKey = s"elementType=${globalIndex.elementType}:indexName=${globalIndex.indexName}"
          cacheKey -> globalIndex
        })
        ls
      }

      ls // return ls
    } else {
      ls
    }
  }
```

~~I changed the code to return `ls` as shown below and confirmed that it works without problems.~~
